### Your own MCP server

This project also ships its own MCP server (`src/{{ pkg }}/mcp/server.py`)
exposing: **{{ spec.effective_mcp_tools | join(', ') }}**. Run it standalone,
or connect it to Claude / Copilot / Codex:

```bash
uv run {{ spec.slug }}-mcp-server                       # run the server
uv run python -m {{ pkg }}.mcp.client_demo               # sample client
claude mcp add {{ spec.slug }}-tools -- uv run {{ spec.slug }}-mcp-server
```

It's already wired into `mcp_servers.json` as `{{ spec.slug }}-tools`, so the
agent(s) in this project can call these tools too.
